The paper discusses lossless compression techniques for 2D sources such as images, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and data compression (cs.DC). The proposed technique involves encoding the source in blocks, which is related to the field of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also deals with analyzing the average codeword length, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CV).
